</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1193,1746,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1674,1951]" box="[199,1193,1746,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1746,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Habitat.</emphasis>
Marine; coarse sand at a depth of 
<quantity box="[683,794,1747,1771]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20–30 cm</quantity>
between low and mid-water levels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,913,1782,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1674,1951]" box="[199,913,1782,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1782,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Distribution.</emphasis>
So far the species appears to be endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[848,909,1782,1807]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="496" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1674,1951]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1818,1843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C." box="[323,556,1818,1843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" pagination="169" refId="ref9261" refString="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C. (2004) Gastrotricha. In: Fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, pp. 169." type="book chapter" year="2004">Naidu &amp; Rao (2004)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the species to be present also in North America (Florida); however, we could not find any original reference in this regard. Very likely the record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao" authorityYear="1970" box="[1116,1403,1854,1879]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="hexadactylis">
<emphasis box="[1116,1403,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Macrodasys hexadactylis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Florida (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hummon, W. D." box="[291,462,1891,1915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" refId="ref8725" refString="Hummon, W. D. (2010) Global Distribution of Marine Gastrotricha. Available from: http: // www. gastrotricha. unimore. it / checklist. htm (accessed 15 October 2018)" type="url" year="2010">Hummon 2010</bibRefCitation>
) may have generated the confusion. Consequently 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao &amp; Ganapati" authorityYear="1968" box="[1035,1192,1890,1915]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Cephalodasyidae" genus="Mesodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="hexapodus">
<emphasis box="[1035,1192,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">M. hexapodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[281,343,1926,1951]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
